	abstract     = {In order to maintain a desired formation of multiple autonomous underwater vehicles (multi-AUVs), one important task is to localize all AUVs. This paper addresses a passive localization method which uses the acoustic signals from the support ship and their own. A simple time-delay estimation (TDE) algorithm based on Pad\'{e} approximation and recursive extended least square (REL-S) method is proposed to process the acoustic signals such that the difference between the time-delays can be estimated. By solving the equation of the time-difference-of-arrive (TDOA) between AUVs and the support ship, the relative positions between the AUVs can be obtained. Finally, some simulations are provided to show the effectiveness of the new method.},
